1.Define responsive design and its importance in modern web development.
->Responsive design is a web development approach that ensures websites automatically adjust their layout, content, and elements based on the screen size and device being used.

2.Explain the role of media queries in responsive design.
->Media queries are a key CSS feature that allow a website to change its layout and styles based on the characteristics of the user’s device, such as screen size, resolution, or orientation.

3.Describe how viewport settings affect mobile displays.
->The viewport is the visible area of a web page on a device’s screen. On mobile devices, the viewport is much smaller than on desktops, so web pages must be scaled and adjusted properly to fit these smaller screens.